rvices company contents  early life and education  career  board memberships  philanthropy  recognition and awards  references early life and educationedit bansal was born in patiala india and emigrated with his parents to the united states when he was two years old the family settled in the northern virginia suburbs of washington dc he attended lake braddock secondary school in burke virginia where he was a valedictorian his father ved bansal came to the united states in  with  his fathers work ethic and emphasis on math and science in childhood has been cited as the foundation for his later education and career bansal received a bachelor of science in electrical engineering from mit and a master of science in computer science from the johns hopkins university careeredit directly out of college sanju bansal worked for the technology and management consulting firm booz allen hamilton in  with mit classmates michael saylor and thomas spahr bansal cofounded microstrategy bansal helped build microstrategy with no venture capital often working  to  hours per week to get the company off the ground during this time the company experienced rapid growth increasing revenues by  every year between  and  in june  microstrategy had its initial public offering and on its first day of trading the stock price doubled by march  the company had a market cap of approximately  billion making bansal and other company leaders billionaires on paper later that month microstrategy announced that it would restate its financial results for the preceding two years which resulted in an investigation by the us securities and exchange commission in december  saylor bansal and the companys former cfo settled with the sec without admitting wrongdoing by each paying  in fines the officers also paid a combined total of  million in disgorgement subsequently the companys stock price plummeted from a high of  in march to a low of  by december  as chief operating officer bansal played a significant role in getting microstrategy back on its feet he was instrumental in raising more than  million in the following  months to keep the company going and expanding business into china in  the company employed more than  people worldwide and reported revenue of  million in  as of  the company has operations in  countries in  bansal founded hunch analytics which currently contains two portfolio companies navhealth a healthcare data analytics firm and equate analytics a performance marketing firm board membershipsedit bansal serves as a board member for the following companies csra nyse csra as a member of the board of directors since january  csra a fortune  company with over b in revenue serves the us government by modernizing computer systems protecting networks and assets and improving government effectiveness and efficiency the advisory board company nasdaq abco as member of the board of directors since november  from  the advisory board company’s revenue grew  each year and in  and  modernhealthcare named the advisory board company to its second annual “healthcares hottest” recognition program which honors the fastest growing companies and organizations in the industry as measured by revenue growth clarabridge as member of the board of directors since march  clarabridge utilizes sentiment and text analytics to automatically collect categorize and report on structured and unstructured data everquote as member of the board of directors since may  everquote is a quantitative internet marketing firm focused on applying sophisticated mathematics and enterprise class technology to its partners online customer acquisition programs vestmark as a member of the board since january  vestmark offers a technology platform to enable broker dealers investment managers rias bank trusts and other financial firms to deliver wealth management and advisory solutions verato as a member of the board of directors since january  verato is a saasbased platform that cleans updates and links customer records within and across systems previous boards microstrategy as vicechairman of the board of directors bansal served on the microstrategy board from september  to november  cvent nyse cvt as cofounder and member of the cvent board of directors since  providing the seed capital for the eventmanagement software company bansal is credited with helping cvent navigate the burst of the dotcom bubble and more recently pushing the firm to expand into mobile and social applications in july  cvent secured  million in venture capital financing from new enterprise associates and insight venture partners with greenspring associates also participating on august   cvent had its initial public offering with a price of  and bansal owned approximately  million shares or  of the company on april   cvent announced that the company was acquired by vista equity partners for  billion philanthropyedit in  bansal established the sanju k bansal foundation the foundation tagline is helping people help themselves through improved access to information the foundation is known for its financial sponsorship of wamu  american university radio wamu  is the leading public radio station for npr news and information in the greater washington dc area the bansal foundation contributes to organizations including the washington humane society the network for teaching entrepreneurship nfte upakar indianamerican scholarship foundation the kailash goyal foundation the global india fund and wolf trap national park for the performing arts in may  the kailash goyal foundation with aid from the bansal foundation opened the jk shanti charitable clinic a free clinic to support the medical needs of the villagers and laborers near the indian town of panchkula the clinic treats approximately  people a year bansal served on the board of directors for wolf trap foundation for the performing arts from  to  located near vienna virginia wolf trap is the only national park dedicated to the performing arts recognition and awardsedit in  bansal received the washington business journals outstanding directors award for his work with cvent in   and  bansal was named one of the washingtonians  top tech titans a list honoring the top  leaders of washington dcs tech world in  he was named one of the washingtonians style setters referencesedit  salter chuck  the reeducation of an internet ceo fast company retrieved    form k for microstrategy inc yahoo finance  retrieved    cvent announces pricing of initial public offering herald online  retrieved    forbes profile of sanju bansal forbes  retrieved    martin kady ii in the shadows washington business journal november    chuck salter the reeducation of an internet ceo fast company december    carbasho tracy  turnarounds are possible with strong guiding hand indus business journal retrieved    glasser jeff  from the ground up and up the washington post retrieved    initial public offerings key data nasdaq  retrieved    kaplan david a  microstrategys boy king grows up fortune retrieved    carbasho tracy  turnarounds are possible with strong guiding hand indus business journal retrieved    hilzenrath david s  for microstrategy a matter of timing the washington post retrieved    lau debra  forbes faces michael saylor forbes retrieved    historical prices microstrategy inc mstr yahoo finance retrieved    flook bill   years in  microstrategy restated two years of earnings washington business journal retrieved    jeff clabaugh microstrategy reorganizes management washington business journal october    microstrategy about us  microstrategy announces fourth quarter  financial results  microstrategy about us  advisory board company abco sanju k bansal independent director morningstar retrieved    healthcare’s hottest for   of the healthcare industry’s fastest growing companies modernhealthcare  retrieved    clarabridge adds microstrategys sanju bansal to board of directors  everquote appoints sanju bansal and john lunny to its board of directo